race.description: Pat Murphy Racing Country Boosted Mdn Plate
race.comment: DEE DEE EXPRESS (3) wound up strongly to finish 1.3L adrift over 1000m at Canberra on debut. The speed-bred mare is in the sharp Matt Dale yard and is sure to have come on. She sets a decent standard. GLENN'S LEGACY (5) returned from a spell at Moruya three weeks ago and was in the firing line before tiring late beaten 3.5L. Strips fitter and Brock Ryan stays aboard. He's been kept up to the mark with a trial and is sure to stick on better. STORMY REIGN (7) has had two runs for the Pepper yard and didn't have much luck first-up. Maps better today and at her first two starts she showed promise when in the care of Bjorn Baker. Quick improvement is likely. Wary of WHOOPI DO (8), who debuts for the Potter yard with Collett a key jockey engagement. She was beaten 1L in a recent Canberra trial and maps for the run of the race.
